<#tt0094764-john_snyder>
	schema:about <#tt0094764>;
	schema:author "john_snyder";
	schema:dateCreated "Thu Apr 13 2000 00:00:00 GMT+0200 (Mitteleuropäische Sommerzeit)";
	schema:reviewRating 8;
	schema:headline " An Undiscovered Gem";
	schema:reviewBody "What can you really say about this movie to someone who hasn't seen it? It sounds like a cheesy idea and a poor plot for a film in a postapocalyptic world the only sport left is a brutal game of steal the bacon played by hardworn gladiators wearing leather chains and rubber. Not exactly King Lear is it? Who would watch this crap?But once you do it's an amazing experience. The game called Jugging is excellently portrayed leaving you begging to know more about its rules and the Mad Maxesque setting is brilliantly shown the futility of the world is never shoved in your face the characters are allowed to simply exist in it. Rutger Haur stars as a hard man who's very tired of his hard life and Joan Chen shines as a young girl who bites off just about all she can chew. Delroy Lindo and Vincent D'onofrio give stellar backup performances.The movie actually plays like a standard sports flick a ragtag team of misfits put aside their differences and overcome immense obstacles to get a shot at the champions in a DavidvsGoliath battle. We've all seen it before. The difference here is the sport is an vicious amalgam of football wrestling and goodol'fashioned asskicking and the world they play it in is a dead hellhole.There's not a lot you can say about this flick to get someone to want to watch it except just try it. After you do you WILL be glad you did.And damned if I didn't want to try Jugging after it was over. ".

