<#tt0094764-Books_8>
	schema:about <#tt0094764>;
	schema:author "Books_8";
	schema:dateCreated "Tue Oct 05 1999 00:00:00 GMT+0200 (Mitteleuropäische Sommerzeit)";
	schema:headline " A far better film than it should be";
	schema:reviewBody "This movie should be an okay post appocalyptic actionadventure on a level with Steel Dawn. It's not. Set in a post apocalyptic world athletes known as Juggers travel from one village to the next playing an ultraviolent sport called simply the game. The game is a bizarre derivative of football where the quick tries to put a dog skull on a stake.Joan Chen plays the role of a young quick who joins a traveling team of juggers captained by an older man Rutger Hauer. Chen plays the role with as much or more intensity than any other role I have seen her in. Hauer is better in this role than anything else I have ever seen him in. Everyone in this film seemed to believe they could earn an academy award even with such a bizarre plot and played their parts with so much heart and skill that you truly care about the characters and what happens to them.The movie is so well done that by the end of the film you even understand the rules of the game.".

